     <h2>Understanding a changing world and how it impacts our natural resources, our livelihoods, and our communities.</h2> 
     <h2 class="section_hdr">The CLU Mission Area includes these activities:</h2> 
     <div class="mission"> 
      <table> 
       <tbody>
        <tr> 
         <td class="borderright borderbottom"> 
          <div class="title">
           <a href="http://www.usgs.gov/climate_landuse/carbon_seq/">Carbon Sequestration</a>
          </div> <a href="http://www.usgs.gov/climate_landuse/carbon_seq/"><img width="130" height="130" src="images/carbon_sml.jpg" alt="Trees in a forest"></a> <br>Carbon Sequestration scientists assess current and potential carbon sequestration in ecosystems and geologic formations. </td> 
         <td class="borderbottom"> 
          <div class="title">
           <a href="http://www.usgs.gov/climate_landuse/clu_rd/">Climate Research &amp; Development</a>
          </div> <a href="http://www.usgs.gov/climate_landuse/clu_rd/"><img width="130" height="130" src="images/r&amp;d_sml.jpg" alt="Scientist in the mountains performing field measurements"></a> <br>Climate R&amp;D conducts fundamental research on the processes and impacts of climate and land-use change. </td> 
        </tr> 
        <tr> 
         <td class="borderright borderbottom"> 
          <div class="title">
           <a href=" http://eros.usgs.gov/">Earth Resources Observation and Science Center</a>
          </div> <a href=" http://eros.usgs.gov/"><img width="130" height="130" src="images/eros_sml.jpg" alt="Satellite over examples of image products"></a> <br>EROS is the NationÂ’s archive of global land imagery and the provider of information and knowledge for understanding how a changing Earth affects people and nature. </td> 
         <td class="borderbottom"> 
          <div class="title">
           <a href="http://www.usgs.gov/climate_landuse/lcs/">Land Change Science</a>
          </div> <a href="http://www.usgs.gov/climate_landuse/lcs/"><img width="130" height="130" src="images/lcs_sml.jpg" alt="Scientist in grasslands performing field studies"></a> <br>LCS researches the spatial patterns, processes and consequences of changes in land use, land condition and land cover. </td> 
        </tr> 
        <tr> 
         <td class="borderright borderbottom"> 
          <div class="title">
           <a href="http://remotesensing.usgs.gov">Land Remote Sensing</a>
          </div> <a href="http://remotesensing.usgs.gov"><img width="130" height="130" src="images/lrs_sml.jpg" alt="Four Decades of Earth Imaging"></a> <br>Oversees the management of the Landsat Missions and Land Imagery Archive located at EROS Center. LRS supports the development of the new remote sensing science data products and helps ensure land remote sensing data continuity. </td> 
         <td class="borderbottom"> 
          <div class="title">
           <a href="http://nccwsc.usgs.gov">National Climate Change &amp; Wildlife Science Center</a>
          </div> <a href="http://nccwsc.usgs.gov"><img width="130" height="130" src="images/nccwsc_sml.jpg" alt="Bird in the Grass"></a> <br>NCCWSC provides managers with information addressing the impacts of climate change on wildlife and habitats. </td> 
        </tr> 
        <tr> 
         <td colspan="2"> 
          <div class="title">
           <a href="http://uas.usgs.gov">National Unmanned Aircraft Systems Project Office</a>
          </div> <a href="http://uas.usgs.gov"><img width="130" height="130" src="images/uas_sml.jpg" alt="UAS in flight"></a> <br>The National UAS Project Office supports the safe, efficient, and cost-effective adoption of UAS technology into the research and operational activities of the DOI. </td> 
        </tr> 
       </tbody>
      </table> 
     </div> 
